  "title": "Logistics Officer",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><p>The Logistics Officer<strong> </strong>is responsible for managing and overseeing the efficient movement of goods, materials, and services within the company’s supply chain. This includes coordinating transportation, inventory management, warehousing, and ensuring timely delivery to meet operational and customer demands.<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /><br /><strong>Inventory & Warehouse:</strong> Managing stock levels, warehouse operations, and equipment.<br /><strong>Procurement:</strong> Liaising with suppliers, negotiating terms, and managing contracts.<br /><strong>Transportation:</strong> Scheduling deliveries, coordinating transport, and optimizing routes.<br /><strong>Coordination:</strong> Working across departments (operations, sales, etc.) for smooth operations.<br /><strong>Reporting:</strong> Preparing data and reports on logistics performance, KPIs, and inventory.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements :</strong><br /><br />1) Using data to identify bottlenecks and optimize storage space or transport costs.<br />2) Effectively communicating with diverse stakeholders, from warehouse staff to international suppliers.<br />3) Strong organizational skills</p>",
